And all the neighbors came around and said, "Well, that's great, isn't it?".

17
00:01:05.710 --> 00:01:06.950
And the farmer said, "Maybe".

18
00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:11.790
The next day, his son, who was attempting to tame one of the horses,

19
00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:14.840
Was riding it and he was thrown from the horse and broke his leg.

20
00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:19.600
And all the neighbors came around that evening and said, "Well, that's too bad, isn't it?".

21
00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:21.850
And the farmer said, "Maybe".

22
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:29.650
The next day, the military officers came around looking for people to join the army, and they rejected his son because he had a broken leg.

23
00:01:30.710 --> 00:01:33.860
So all the neighbors came around that evening and said, "Isn't that wonderful?"

24
00:01:34.670 --> 00:01:35.610
And the farmer said, "Maybe".

25
00:01:37.470 --> 00:01:40.990
The whole process of nature is an integrated process of immense complexity.

26
00:01:42.050 --> 00:01:45.860
It really is impossible to tell whether anything that happens in it is good or bad,

27
00:01:46.060 --> 00:01:48.730
Because you never know what the consequences of a misfortune will be.

28
00:01:49.420 --> 00:01:52.050
And you never know what the consequences of good fortune will be.

29
00:01:53.760 --> 00:02:02.680
One door closes, another one opens. You're up today and you're down tomorrow. It was all good just a week ago.

30
00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:08.450
It was fascinating how one simple decision can spark an unpredictable chain of events,

31
00:02:08.710 --> 00:02:12.570
That range from good to bad or from wonderful to horrific.

32
00:02:14.040 --> 00:02:18.090
For example, a kid grows up in a violent and unpredictable environment.

33
00:02:19.110 --> 00:02:24.560
His parents are abusive drug addicts that give him no love, attention, or guidance in his life as he grows up.

34
00:02:25.730 --> 00:02:32.430
He comes to know despair, pain, sorrow, loneliness, and rage at a very young age,

35
00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:37.090
But even still, he doesn't let his upbringing define him or his future.

36
00:02:37.570 --> 00:02:42.360
He finds a way to teach, take care of and rely on himself so that he doesn't end up like his parents.

37
00:02:43.660 --> 00:02:47.240
After years of getting beat by his parents and witnessing the effects of drug addiction,

38
00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:51.570
He decides that he wants to break the cycle of damaged parents raising damaged children.

39
00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:56.880
So he decides to become a child psychologist and he does social work at local schools and churches.

40
00:02:57.450 --> 00:03:01.470
And now he's a positive influence and a father figure for countless kids in his community,

41
00:03:01.760 --> 00:03:05.160
Keeping them out of trouble and thus saving countless lives in the process.

42
00:03:06.210 --> 00:03:09.840
He's helping kids to understand that even if you can't change your environment at the moment,

43
00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:12.960
You can always choose how you react to your environment.

44
00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:19.470
So was this man growing up in an abusive, toxic environment, a good thing or a bad thing?

